⚡ Quick recovery options

✅ Option 1: Fix mirror (BEST)

Re-run mirror properly:

oc mirror --config=imageset-config.yaml docker://<your-registry>

Make sure:

includes platform: openshift

correct version

no partial mirror



---

✅ Option 2: Temporarily bypass mirror (for recovery)

Edit on node:

vi /etc/containers/registries.conf

Remove mirror override → allow pull from:

quay.io

Then:

systemctl restart crio
systemctl restart kubelet

👉 If cluster comes up → mirror confirmed broken


---

✅ Option 3: Rollback (if rpm-ostree staged)

rpm-ostree rollback
reboot


